Audio samples:

Plucked concert harp tone is from the Versilian Community Sample Library
(VCSL), released under Creative Commons Zero (CC0 1.0, public domain
dedication) by Versilian Studios / Sam Gossner.
https://github.com/sgossner/VCSL
These samples have been trimmed, level-matched, and compressed from the
originals.

Harmonics, pres de la table, nail, xylophonic, and etouffe samples were
recorded by Yijun Lin and are released under Creative Commons Zero (CC0 1.0,
public domain dedication).

No rights are reserved on any of the audio under CC0.

---

Musical glyphs:

Notation symbols (clefs, noteheads, accidentals, and technique signs) are
outlines extracted from the Bravura font, (c) 2021 Steinberg Media Technologies
GmbH, with Reserved Font Name "Bravura", licensed under the SIL Open Font
License, Version 1.1. The full license text and font copyright notice are in
the accompanying OFL.txt file.
https://github.com/steinbergmedia/bravura

The display fonts "Italianno" and "Ephesis" (title and subtitle) are loaded at
run time from Google Fonts and are not distributed with this software; both are
licensed under the SIL Open Font License, Version 1.1 (see OFL.txt).
